<h1>Dakin Reaction</h1>
<p><img src="Dakin.1.gif" width="403" height="55"></p>
<p>The Dakin Reaction allows the preparation of phenols from aryl aldehydes 
or aryl ketones via oxidation with hydrogen peroxide in the presence of 
base. The aryl formate or alkanoate formed as an intermediate is 
subsequently saponified to yield the substituted phenol product.</p>
<p><i>Ortho</i> 
or
<i> para</i> +M substituents (NH<sub>2</sub>, OH) favor this reaction.</p>
<hr>
<h2>Mechanism of the Dakin Reaction</h2>
<p>See <a href="baeyer-villiger-oxidation.shtm">Baeyer-Villiger Oxidation</a>
for the oxidation step.</p>
<div style="margin: 15 0 5 -7; padding: 7 4 7 4; border: 1px solid #DDDDDD; clear:both">
